<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2015-02-12</DATELINE><TITLE>The first case of porcine epidemic diarrhea in Canada</TITLE><BODY>In January, 2014, increased mortality was reported in piglets with acute diarrhea on an Ontario farm. Villus atrophy in affected piglets was confined to the small intestine. Samples of colon content were PCR-positive for porcine epidemic diarrhea virus (PEDV). Other laboratory tests did not detect significant pathogens, confirming this was the first case of PED in Canada.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>